This file defines the main layout for the application's dashboard. It wraps the main content of the dashboard with a persistent sidebar.

### Purpose

The `DashboardLayout` component serves as a structural container for all pages within the `/dashboard` route. It ensures a consistent user experience by always displaying the `Sidebar` alongside the main content area.

### Key Components

*   **`Sidebar`**: Imported from `@/components/ui/sidebar`, this component renders the navigation sidebar.
*   **`children`**: This prop represents the content of the specific dashboard page being rendered.

### Usage

Any component rendered within the `/dashboard` route will automatically be wrapped by this layout.

```tsx
// Example of a dashboard page using the layout
// app/dashboard/page.tsx

import React from 'react';

export default function DashboardPage() {
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>Welcome to your Dashboard</h1>
      <p>This is the main content area.</p>
    </div>
  );
}
```

The `DashboardLayout` will automatically apply the `Sidebar` to the left and render the `DashboardPage` content in the main area, creating a two-column layout.
